## Walkthrough

The PR introduces comprehensive enhancements including a new post-edit code review hook system (PowerShell), Drupal and MDN API scrapers integrated with Weaviate, PostgreSQL migration from SQLite, a Claude Code CLI execution manager with session support, HTTPS reverse proxy (Nginx) configuration, authentication and pause/resume capabilities for the dashboard, and expanded testing infrastructure with VPS deployment support.

## Sequence Diagrams

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User/IDE
    participant Claude as Claude Code
    participant Hook as Post-Edit Hook<br/>(PowerShell)
    participant Linter as Linter<br/>(ruff/eslint)
    participant Output as Hook Output

    User->>Claude: Save/edit file
    Claude->>Hook: Trigger hook with file_path
    Hook->>Hook: Validate file & path
    alt File is Python (.py)
        Hook->>Linter: Run ruff
    else File is TS/JS (.ts/.tsx/.js/.jsx)
        Hook->>Linter: Run eslint via npx
    else Other/Invalid
        Hook->>Hook: Skip (return 0)
    end
    Linter-->>Hook: Issues found or exit code
    Hook->>Hook: Aggregate issues
    alt Issues Found
        Hook->>Output: Print formatted banner<br/>with issue list
    else No Issues
        Hook->>Output: No issues found
    end
    Output-->>Claude: Display results<br/>(non-blocking)
```

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Dashboard as Dashboard Backend
    participant Ingestion as IngestionManager
    participant Drupal as DrupalAPIScraper
    participant Weaviate as Weaviate
    participant Checkpoint as CheckpointManager

    Dashboard->>Ingestion: start_ingestion(types=['drupal'], ..., limit=100)
    Ingestion->>Ingestion: Initialize & validate config
    Ingestion->>Drupal: scrape_drupal_api(config, ..., check_paused)
    Drupal->>Drupal: Fetch entity listings (paginated)
    loop For each entity (with pause checks)
        Drupal->>Ingestion: check_paused() callback
        alt Paused
            Ingestion->>Ingestion: _wait_if_paused()
            Ingestion-->>Dashboard: Emit "ingestion_paused" event
        end
        Drupal->>Drupal: Parse entity metadata
        Drupal->>Drupal: Compute hash & UUID
        Drupal->>Weaviate: Insert entity with embedding
        Checkpoint->>Checkpoint: Save progress (every 10 entities)
    end
    Drupal-->>Ingestion: Complete (entities_processed, entities_inserted)
    Ingestion->>Ingestion: Aggregate stats
    Ingestion-->>Dashboard: Emit "ingestion_complete" event
```

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Frontend Client
    participant Auth as Auth Endpoint
    participant Dashboard as Dashboard API
    participant Claude as ClaudeManager
    participant Process as Claude Process
    participant WebSocket as WebSocket/Socket.IO

    Client->>Auth: POST /api/auth/token<br/>(username, password)
    Auth->>Dashboard: Validate credentials
    Auth-->>Client: Return session token
    Client->>WebSocket: Connect with auth: {token}
    WebSocket->>Dashboard: Validate token
    alt Token Valid
        Dashboard->>Claude: Initialize session
        WebSocket-->>Client: Connected
    else Token Invalid
        WebSocket-->>Client: auth_error
    end
    Client->>Dashboard: POST /api/claude/execute<br/>(prompt, mode='normal'|'yolo')
    Dashboard->>Claude: Start session (new subprocess)
    Claude->>Claude: Spawn Claude CLI process
    Claude->>Process: Stream output in background
    loop While process running
        Process-->>Claude: Read stdout/stderr lines
        Claude->>WebSocket: Emit "claude_output"<br/>(session_id, line)
        WebSocket-->>Client: Receive output line (real-time)
    end
    Process-->>Claude: Exit code
    Claude->>Claude: Finalize session (completed/error/timeout)
    Claude->>WebSocket: Emit "claude_status"<br/>(session_id, status)
    WebSocket-->>Client: Session completed
```

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User
    participant Dashboard as Dashboard<br/>(Service Manager)
    participant Service as Target Service<br/>(Process)
    participant Socket as WebSocket Event

    User->>Dashboard: Click Pause button<br/>(service_id)
    Dashboard->>Service: Send SIGSTOP<br/>(POSIX) or Suspend<br/>(Windows)
    Service-->>Dashboard: Process paused
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: Update state to PAUSED
    Dashboard->>Socket: Emit service_paused event
    Socket-->>User: Show paused badge
    User->>Dashboard: Click Resume button
    Dashboard->>Service: Send SIGCONT<br/>(POSIX) or Resume<br/>(Windows)
    Service-->>Dashboard: Process resumed
    Dashboard->>Dashboard: Update state to RUNNING
    Dashboard->>Socket: Emit service_resumed event
    Socket-->>User: Show running status
```

## Estimated code review effort

**Specific areas requiring careful attention:**

- **PostgreSQL migration and database schema changes** (`api_gateway/config.py`, `api_gateway/models/database.py`, migration scripts): Complex async/sync database interaction patterns, connection pooling configuration, and data migration logic with rollback capabilities. Verify data integrity and error handling paths.
- **Drupal and MDN scraper implementations** (`api_gateway/services/drupal_scraper.py`, `mdn_*_scraper.py`): Intricate HTTP client logic with rate limiting, pagination, pause/cancel hooks, content parsing, and Weaviate integration. Review content extraction patterns and error recovery.
- **Claude execution manager** (`dashboard/backend/claude_manager.py`): Multi-threaded session management, WebSocket integration, subprocess lifecycle control, and timeout handling. Verify thread safety and proper process cleanup.
- **Pause/resume semantics** (`api_gateway/services/code_ingestion.py`, `api_gateway/services/doc_ingestion.py`, `dashboard/backend/ingestion_manager.py`): Cooperative pause checking at multiple pipeline points requires consistent state management and proper unlock mechanisms.
- **Nginx reverse proxy configuration** (`nginx/conf.d/ssdd.conf`, related scripts): Complex SSL/TLS setup, path-based routing to 20+ services, WebSocket support, and security header configurations. Verify port mappings and timeout settings align with backend services.
- **Frontend state management and authentication flow** (`dashboard/frontend/src/hooks/useIngestion.ts`, `useSocket.ts`, `useClaude.ts`): Token-based auth, multiple concurrent real-time event streams, and component-level state coordination with pause/resume/pause ingestion events.
- **Test infrastructure and service orchestration** (`tests/utils/service-orchestrator.ts`, `tests/fixtures/*`, smoke tests): Service startup/health polling logic with retry/backoff, concurrent operations, and VPS-specific environment handling require careful validation of timeout and error thresholds.
- **Embedding model migration** (`api_gateway/services/migrate_embeddings.py`): Full collection deletion and re-ingestion workflow; verify data loss prevention and model availability checks before destructive operations.
